  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (human-error gap probe)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Operator role (perfusionist) is acknowledged in the COU description; however, all validation activities assume correctly formatted boundary-condition inputs and nominal pump-speed set-points. No use-error modes — misentry of flow-rate targets, incorrect speed ramp profiles, or training-gap scenarios — are characterised or linked to any validation result. The single use-error credibility factor is marked not-assessed without supporting justification, leaving the human-error dimension unaddressed.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cou1-hemolysis-req",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cou1-hemolysis-claim",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/morrison-cfd-hemolysis-v2",
