      "acceptanceCriteria": "Representative operator error modes identified and their effect on model predictions bounded.",
      "rationale": "A single gross over-speed scenario (pump speed +10% above maximum nominal) was evaluated and found acceptable. Systematic characterisation of operator error modes — including misentry of flow-rate targets, incorrect speed-ramp sequencing, and errors attributable to training gaps in perfusionist workflows — was not performed. The use-error factor is therefore recorded as not-assessed; no structured use-error analysis or hazard enumeration was conducted to bound the space of plausible operator inputs encountered in clinical deployment."
