    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou1-decision-001",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Seven of thirteen credibility factors are assessed and meet required levels for MRL 2. Six factors are not-assessed, which is acceptable under ASME V&V 40 at this risk level. The use-error factor is not-assessed; the single over-speed scenario evaluated is considered representative of the gross-error boundary. The assessment team accepted the package on the basis that the overall credibility score meets the MRL 2 threshold and that the validated operating envelope covers the nominal COU conditions. The absence of a structured operator-error characterisation was noted but not treated as a blocking finding.",
